bugList
  Sometimes a sentence will use less tenses than the minimum required. This is due to behind the scenes stuff that I can't fix, so just be aware of it.
  <i>anga</i> does not conjugate properly and is listed incorrectly in the dictionary as <i>angsa</i>.
  Some irregular verbs may have the word "TEMP" (or sometimes "TEM") in the verb. <i>Please</i> let me know if you see this!
  Measure word constructions take the case marker on the wrong word.
  Sometimes when the imperative tense is used, the sentence will lack a subject.
  
minTenses = [document.getElementById("minTenses").value]
maxTenses = [document.getElementById("maxTenses").value]
